org.middleheaven.quantity.time
Class Chronology

java.lang.Object
  org.middleheaven.quantity.time.Chronology
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractChronology
public abstract class Chronology
extends java.lang.Object

A definition of how time is computed. All int value correspond to ordinal values (i.e. 1- fisrt, 2- secound, 3-thirs , and so on ...)

milisecondsFor

public abstract long milisecondsFor(boolean lenient,
                                    int year,
                                    int month,
                                    int day)
Transforms a yera, month, day information into milisecounds from 1990, January 1st

Parameters:
lenient - true to use the next possible date if the values conform to a non-existing date, if false throw an exception if the date does not exist.
year - the year
month - the month of the year
day - the day of the month
Returns:
the correspondent milisecounds in the Chronology.
